{
  "text": "Disease-specific mortality is the most appropriate outcome measure in the evaluation of screening effectiveness. Mortality is a population-based measure, and the denominator includes the entire population in the study. Lung cancer mortality in the screened population is the ratio of the number of deaths from lung cancer to the number of personyears of observation. Effectiveness of screening is determined by the reduction in deaths from lung cancer in the screened group versus the control group in a randomized controlled trial (RCT) [CITATION_1] .",
